# identityData

**Instance Property**

The certificate and private key components of the tunneling protocol authentication credential, in PKCS12 format.

## Declaration

```swift
var identityData: Data? { get set }
```

## Discussion

In macOS, the system ignores this property for [doc://com.apple.networkextension/documentation/NetworkExtension/NEVPNProtocolIKEv2] and [doc://com.apple.networkextension/documentation/NetworkExtension/NETunnelProviderProtocol] objects. On iOS, the system ignores this property for [doc://com.apple.networkextension/documentation/NetworkExtension/NETunnelProviderProtocol] objects. In cases where the system ignores this property, set the identity using the [doc://com.apple.networkextension/documentation/NetworkExtension/NEVPNProtocol/identityReference] property.

## Authenticating the user

- **username**: The user name component of the tunneling protocol authentication credential.
- **passwordReference**: A persistent keychain reference to a keychain item containing the password component of the tunneling protocol authentication credential.
- **identityReference**: A persistent keychain reference to a keychain item containing the certificate and private key components of the tunneling protocol authentication credential.
- **identityDataPassword**: The password for the PKCS12 tunneling protocol authentication credentials.
